I just got 203, and tried to start it with my slightly old (136) workspace.
	Since the workspace was somewhat old (I have been away for 3 days) I decided to do a Replace with->Stream element
	on the org.eclipse.swt project to do a "brute-force catchup" and bypass the compare.

	I got an 'Unable To Replace' error dialog saying "Resource is out of sync with the file system: /org.eclipse.swt/bin/org.zip".
	I tried it several times, with the same result.
	It destroyed the old state of my project - there's a whole bunch of stuff missing (and since I had autobuild on, I had a zillion errors).

	I decided to delete the project and try adding it from scratch.
	Eclipse would not let me delete the project, because it said it was out of sync with the file system.
	But I really want to delete this project, because it is whacked and broken somehow.
	I should be able to delete it, even if it is out of sync with the repository.

	In case it helps any, here are the various walkbacks in the .log file from me trying to delete the project, and then I tried
	deleting various resources inside the project as well, with no luck.

	(I was able to do a catchup, even though I did not care about the changes, so at least my workspace was not scrapped).
